Interface UiWidgetWindow

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AbstractValidatableObject, Accessibility, AttributeReadAriaRole, AttributeReadClosable, AttributeReadDisposed, AttributeReadEnabled, AttributeReadHtmlId, AttributeReadId<String>, AttributeReadMaximizable, AttributeReadMaximized, AttributeReadMode, AttributeReadModeFixed, AttributeReadModified, AttributeReadMovable, AttributeReadPosition, AttributeReadPrimaryStyle, AttributeReadResizable, AttributeReadStringTitle, AttributeReadStyles, AttributeReadStylesAdvanced, AttributeReadTitle<String>, AttributeReadTooltip, AttributeReadVisible, AttributeReadVisibleRecursive, AttributeWriteClosable, AttributeWriteDisposed, AttributeWriteEnabled, AttributeWriteHtmlId, AttributeWriteId<String>, AttributeWriteMaximizable, AttributeWriteMaximized, AttributeWriteMode, AttributeWriteModeFixed, AttributeWriteMovable, AttributeWritePosition, AttributeWritePrimaryStyle, AttributeWriteResizable, AttributeWriteStringTitle, AttributeWriteStyles, AttributeWriteStylesAdvanced, AttributeWriteTitle<String>, AttributeWriteTooltip, AttributeWriteVisible, AttributeWriteVisibleAdvanced, UiFeature, UiFeatureEvent, UiFeatureMessages, UiFeatureMode, UiFeatureOpenClose, UiWidget, UiWidgetAbstractComposite, UiWidgetAbstractDialogWindow, UiWidgetAbstractWindow, UiWidgetComposite<UiWidgetRegular>, UiWidgetDynamicComposite<UiWidgetRegular>, UiWidgetMultiComposite<UiWidgetRegular>, UiWidgetNative
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractUiWidgetWindow, UiWidgetWindowGwt

    public interface UiWidgetWindow
extends UiWidgetAbstractDialogWindow, UiWidgetNative
    This is the interface for a base window widget that represents a regular window. Such window is a non-modal window is typically located inside the UiWidgetMainWindow (MDI).
    Since:
    1.0.0
    Author:
    Joerg Hohwiller (hohwille at users.sourceforge.net)
